race.comment: WELL TIMED (6) brave in defeat from the wide barrier when he loomed strongly for a sound second over 1400m at this track. Stretches to the 1500m for the first time and gets map favours with Rawiller engaged. Will sit off the good speed and launch late. ROCK EMPIRE (7) comes out of the same race as WELL TIMED, after given the gun run for a close-up fourth over the 1400m here. Winning rider back aboard and comes here in peak condition. KINTYRE (2) drops in class and will relish the sting out of the ground from the good draw. Gets Bourke's 2kg claim and can return to form. WAIMARIE (8) classy mare who grows a leg on the heavy surface. Has a solid second-up record and goes into the exotics.
